Sri Lanka 's Marine Police to Protect President
COLOMBO , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- Sri Lanka 's Police Marine Division , which was set up in August this year to combat narcotics and piracy activities , has now been deployed in support of the Presidential Security Division , police sources said Thursday .
The sources said the boats of the division have been deployed to patrol the Beira lake which surrounds the president 's official residence " Temple Trees . "
The rest of the staff , about 40 men strong , will be deployed within " Temple Trees " .
The original plan had been to deploy the boats and men in Galle , Negombo , Kalpitiya , Chilaw and Delft for anti-smuggling operations .
